¬import il from "../../../_shared/variables/imageLinks"


7. The vscode installer dialogue is displayed showing the licence agreement.
8. Click the **I accept the agreement** to enable the **Next** button. *- red circle* 
9. Then click the **Next** button. *- green circle* 

{{::il.Vscode_InstallDialogueStart_img}}

10. The dialogue displays the **Select Destination Location** view.
11. Unless you want to install vscode somewhere other than the default location click **Next**. *- red circle* 

{{::il.Vscode_InstallDialogueLocation_img}}

12. The dialogue displays the **Select Start Menu Folder** view.
13. Click **Next**. *- red circle* 

{{::il.Vscode_InstallDialogueLocation_img}}

14. The dialogue displays the **Select Additional Tasks** view.
15. If they are not already selected select the following - they make opening files from File Explorer easier: *- red circle* 
    - **Add "Open with Code" action to Windows Explorer file context menu**
    - **Add "Open with Code" action to Windows Explorer directory context menu**
16. Click **Next**. *- green circle* 

{{::il.Vscode_InstallDialogueTasks_img}}

17. The installation will take a couple of minutes and when finished dialogue displays the **Ready to Install** view.
18. Click **Install**. *- green circle* 

{{::il.Vscode_InstallDialogueSummary_img}}

17. The installation will take a couple of minutes and when finished dialogue displays the following view.
18. If the checkbox **Launch Visual Studio Code** is checked then vscode is launched when you click the **Finish** button. *- green circle* 
19. Click **Finish** button. *- red circle* 

{{::il.Vscode_InstallDialogueCompleted_img}}

20. If the checkbox **Launch Visual Studio Code** was checked vscode launches. 

{{::il.Vscode_FreshlyInstalled_img}}

